The paper deals with dynamic channel and rate selection in cognitive radio systems, which involves optimization and decision-making in the presence of uncertainty. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes algorithms that exploit the inherent structure of the throughput, which suggests that it may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with cognitive radio systems, which suggests that it may also belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category.
